  "dek": "This article explores the unique dynamics of doing business in Japan, particularly focusing on the deeply ingrained relationship between Japanese salarymen and their employers.  The author, a long-term resident with extensive experience in both traditional Japanese companies and startups, describes this relationship as one of intense loyalty and dedication from the employee in exchange for comprehensive security and stability provided by the company.  The author cautions against essentializing Japanese culture while highlighting the challenges this unique employer-employee relationship poses for startups and foreign businesses operating within Japan.",
